--<br>
well, 1 has not happened in Iraq and isnt even close to happening.  Not only do we have inspectors in there right now making sure of that, but the US knows through other intelligence that Iraq has more or less given up on making nukes on their own.  Yes, they have tried to buy them, unsuccessfuly.  N. Korea is a MUCH bigger threat than Iraq is if that is your worry Zolina - why are we not at war there?  I'll tell you why, because it is not necessary.  Just as it is not necessary to go to war in Iraq.  See my above post for my reasons why I can hold this view but not say &quot;republicans are bad, pres bush is bad, etc&quot;  I don't like Pres. Bush for his economic and health care policy.  That and the fact that he uses propaganda to get the US people to go along with him.  It's an old trick...  blame my history classes in college for enlightening me on <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The receptivity of the great masses is very limited, their intelligence is small, but their power of forgetting is enormous. In consequence of these facts, all effective propaganda must be limited to a very few points and must harp on these in slogans until the last member of the public understands what you want him to understand by your slogan. As soon as you sacrifice this slogan and try to be many-sided, the effect will piddle away, for the crowd can neither digest nor retain the material offered. In this way the result is weakened and in the end entirely cancelled out. -- Adolf Hitler, chapter six of Mein Kampf<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
EDIT #2 :  Gimily, your point is mine exactly from about 2 posts ago.  I think pres bush is playing a heavy hand.  If for some reason he is jumps the gun unnecessarily, the people of the US will hold him responsible for his actions.  If he chooses to go to war, and it is justified, then the american people will see that.  I am just as much against people saying &quot;Nuke the bastards.&quot; than i am against &quot;Peace rules, lets go sing kumbiayh.&quot;  My main worry is if Bush+cabinet make the wrong decision to go to war.  I hope that will not be the case and if they do go to war that there is concrete evidence and not &quot;Saddam is a bad guy.&quot;<br>
<br>
EDIT #3:  Vatikus:  So i'm media moron #0002123454  ??  What is your overly educated opinion based on?  You a member of the CIA (or other intellegence gathering agency) working on this project?  No, you're going off the media as much as I am.  I just hold a different opinion than you.<br>
