<br>
its like tornados.  nobody runs around trying to control tornados.  they pop up we know why but we dont know how to stop it.<br>
<br>
<br>
nobody can fix the instability in iraq.  anything you do to that country destabilizes something else.  <br>
<br>
the logic above of we have to conquer rogue states so that we can be safe presupposes the aftermath is stable.<br>
<br>
Some things are inevitable.  they have to come.  the world has chaos and consequences.  there is wealth and one border over there is poverty.  there is peace and one border over there is unrest.   nothing in human existance says anything else then this is the consequence of human civilization.  Its certainly not the consequence of individual leaders.<br>
<br>
the idea that you can wipe out all the instability in the world by focusing on administrations is false.  there is going to be instability in the world.  iraq is the perfect case.  iraq will be iraq after we leave.   it will not be a democracy.  it will be a shit hole with alot of oil.  theres no fixing it.  it has all the prerequisites to be a rogue state from now till the end of time.<br>
<br>
Its action for actions sake.  it does little to attack iraq.  saddam will live in a different face.   we always say that iraq isnt our enemy. iraq is the enemy if your enemy is instability.  Saddam didnt make iraq unstable.  iraq has been that way.  we hate saddam for representing what cant be fixed.<br>
<br>
