Just to clarify: <br>
<br>
Yugoslavia - according to press was managed predominantly by Europe.  I understand that the majority of press stuff is incorrect.  <br>
<br>
WW2 - Again, the term 'we' used as we Americans winning the war against Japan.  Yet again, I remind people that it was the allies (Europe, Scandanavia, Africa, Russia, China and America) that defeated the Nazi Regime (and the suppliers of advanced technology to Japan) that caused the catalyst to allow the U.S. to strike the killing blow. <br>
<br>
Without the catalyst, it would have been a disaster.<br>
<br>
Afganistan - Again the term 'We' as American.  Fact is, Afganistan's own won the ground assault as they are trained for that terrain, America supplied the air support and part ground force.  If in the event that it did not have Afgan support, there was a high possibility that this would be another Vietnam.   Again according to the press, the U.S. equipment had difficulty in the harsh environment, which I would have thought is a high possibility taking into account that when Hitler invaded Russia and his equipment froze over.  <br>
